.RS
.PP
Opens a handle to a tar file on the server, associated with \fIChannelPid\fR. The handle can be used for remote tar creation and extraction. The actual writing and reading is performed by calls to erl_tar:add/3,4 and \fIerl_tar:extract/2\fR. Note: The \fIerl_tar:init/3\fR function should not be called, that one is called by this open_tar function.

.PP
For code examples see Section SFTP Client with TAR Compression in the ssh Users Guide.

.PP
The \fIcrypto\fR mode option is explained in the data types section above, see Crypto operations for open_tar. Encryption is assumed if the \fIMode\fR contains \fIwrite\fR, and decryption if the \fIMode\fR contains \fIread\fR.


