\fB                          {eof, Offset} |\fR
\fB                          bof | cur | eof,\fR
\fB                      Timeout :: timeout(),\fR
\fB                      Offset :: integer(),\fR
\fB                      NewPosition :: integer(),\fR
\fB                      Error :: {error, reason()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the file position of the file referenced by \fIHandle\fR. Returns \fI{ok, NewPosition}\fR (as an absolute offset) if successful, otherwise \fI{error, reason()}\fR. \fILocation\fR is one of the following:

Offset
.RS 2
The same as 
\fI{bof, Offset}\fR.

.RE

{bof, Offset}
.RS 2
Absolute offset.


.RE

{cur, Offset}
.RS 2
Offset from the current position.


.RE

{eof, Offset}
.RS 2
Offset from the end of file.


.RE

bof | cur | eof
.RS 2
The same as eariler with 
\fIOffset\fR 0, that is, \fI{bof, 0} | {cur, 0} | {eof, 0}\fR.

.RE


