\fB                       {ok, pid(), ssh:connection_ref()} |\fR
\fB                       {error, reason()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Starts new ssh channel for communicating with the SFTP server.

.PP
Starts an ssh channel when first argument is a connection reference.

.PP
Equivalent to start_channel(Host, 22, UserOptions) when first argument is recognized as network host.

.PP
Otherwise, first argument is treated as a network socket which will be used for establishing new SSH connection. New connection reference will be used for starting an SSH channel.

.PP
The returned \fIpid\fR for this process is to be used as input to all other API functions in this module.

.PP
See also (\fIstart_channel/3\fR).


.RE
